# A person from [[Wales]]; a native or inhabitant of [[Wales]]; a [[Welsh]] person.

====Usage notes====
* The term functions as a (possibly somewhat uncommon or nonstandard) singular form of the collective noun ‘Welsh’, and as an ungendered alternative to ‘Welshman’ and ‘Welshwomen’.
* The plural ''Walians'' is found especially in the compounds ''North Walians'' and ''South Walians''.

